{"TAW":[{"def":"To push; to tug; to tow.","pos":""}],"TAWDRILY":[{"def":"In a tawdry manner.","pos":""}],"TAWDRINESS":[{"def":"Quality or state of being tawdry.","pos":""}],"TAWDRY":[{"def":"Bought at the festival of St.","pos":""},{"def":"Very fine and showy in colors, without taste or elegance; having an excess of showy ornaments without grace; cheap and gaudy; as, a tawdry dress; tawdry feathers; tawdry colors.","pos":""}],"TAWER":[{"def":"One who taws; a dresser of white leather.","pos":""}],"TAWERY":[{"def":"A place where skins are tawed.","pos":""}],"TAWNINESS":[{"def":"The quality or state of being tawny.","pos":""}],"TAWNY":[{"def":"Of a dull yellowish brown color, like things tanned, or persons who are sunburnt; as, tawny Moor or Spaniard; the tawny lion.","pos":""}],"TAWS":[{"def":"A leather lash, or other instrument of punishment, used by a schoolmaster.","pos":""}]}